      <!-- About Section -->
      <section id="about" class="about section">
        <div class="container">
          <div class="row gy-4">
            <div
              class="col-lg-6 content"
              data-aos="fade-up"
              data-aos-delay="100"
            >
              <p class="who-we-are">OUR STORY</p>
              <h3>A world with zero furniture waste</h3>
              <p class="fst-italic">
                In a world where the furniture industry is essential for
                creating comfort in our spaces, the industry's impact on the
                environment is often overlooked. In the Netherlands alone,
                millions of kilograms of furniture are discarded annually, with
                only 10% recycled. The rest ends up in landfills, contributing
                to a growing environmental burden.
              </p>
              <p>
                Our mission is towards zero furniture waste by helping furniture
                producers simplify end-of-life management to reduce landfill
                waste. We optimise end-to-end waste solutions and digital tools
                to ensure responsible supply chains with the goal of closing the
                loop on furniture waste. Our solution unfolds in two major
                phases with the initial focus on extending the lifespan of
                furniture products. We do this by connecting discarded furniture
                from consumers and businesses with recycling companies to ensure
                items are collected and processed in a circular manner. This
                phase directly addresses the challenges of disposal by making it
                accessible and hassle-free. Building on this foundation,
                FurnZero will also offer a one-stop data portal to increase
                supply chain transparency using AI and blockchain. This will
                engage supply chain stakeholders across the furniture industry
                to identify lifecycle inefficiencies, from material composition,
                waste generation, and end life management.
              </p>
            </div>

